  "prompt": "Are all caterpillars butterflies?",
  "response": "Not all caterpillars become butterflies. Caterpillars are the larval stage of insects in the order Lepidoptera, which includes both butterflies and moths. While all butterfly larvae (caterpillars) will eventually pupate and emerge as butterflies, some caterpillars belong to moth species and will develop into moths instead. Therefore, while all butterflies have caterpillars, not all caterpillars are butterflies; some are moths.",
